title: How about calming these duststorms?
tags: holtext_complete
new-page: true
on-arrival: example_type = "How about calming these duststorms?"; info_last = "Dust storms" if info_dust_storms = 0; info_dust_storms = 1

Me: [+ example_type +]

Facilyn: A good place to start. Do you have any idea what is really driving them?

Before you can answer, the teahouse door shudders inward and bangs shut again.

A man in a sand-colored field coat stands there for a moment, breathing hard. Fine dust clings to his eyebrows and the seams of his sleeves. Under one arm he carries a weatherproof map tube. In the other hand is a cloth bundle gone dark at the corners.

Facilyn: Neral. You made it in.

Ranger Neral: Barely.

He notices you, gives a short nod, and puts the bundle on the table. When he unwraps it, several gray grass stems roll onto the wood beside a dusting of black ash.

Ranger Neral: Eastern flats. Fresh from the miracle reserve.

Facilyn glances toward the window. Outside, the late light is copper-grey. A delivery drone passes low over the quay, then vanishes into a sheet of airborne dust.

Facilyn: That storm is coming off the eastern flats.

Ranger Neral: And the papers will blame heat, wind, or bad luck. They never blame the management plan.

Facilyn: You work there?

Ranger Neral: Senior ranger. Public tours, fire reports, erosion transects, all of it.

He taps one of the stems. It clicks like brittle bone.

Ranger Neral: No farming. No settlements. No managed herds. Pure rewilding. Protected more carefully than almost anywhere else in the region.

Facilyn: Which is exactly why this is useful.

She looks at you.

Facilyn: If you want to choose a wise action later, do not begin by grabbing the first fix that sounds impressive. Begin by understanding the failure properly.

