@duststorm_ask_fire
title: Ask about the ash and the burns
max-visits: 1

Me: And the ash?

Ranger Neral unclips the map tube and rolls out a reserve map far enough to show several black-marked blocks on the eastern flats.

Ranger Neral: Burn zones. Last month's line.

Ranger Neral: When the old gray material builds up, headquarters authorizes prescribed burns. The official language is always the same: reduce fuel load, stimulate fresh growth, restore vigor.

Facilyn: Fire removes the symptom beautifully.

Ranger Neral: For about five minutes.

Facilyn: Then it burns litter, exposes soil, and leaves the surface open to sun, wind, raindrop impact, runoff, and evaporation. In a brittle environment, that is a dangerous bargain.

Ranger Neral: After a burn, the reserve looks tidier in photographs. Then the next dust storm comes off the flats and blows the accounting into town.

Facilyn: So the burn treats the visible symptom of old gray grass while making the deeper weakness worse.

