@duststorm_ask_rewilding
title: Ask why rewilding is too slow here
max-visits: 1

Me: If the reserve is left alone long enough, would it not eventually recover?

Ranger Neral looks toward the dark window.

Ranger Neral: Perhaps in a thousand years. Perhaps longer. The ministry never puts that part in bold print.

Facilyn: That is the trouble with the word rewilding. People hear it and imagine a fast moral correction. But climate still governs the pace.

Facilyn: In the eastern flats, biological decay is slow. Succession from bare soil is slow. If the ground stays exposed and the dead grass keeps oxidising upright, the land can decline on a timescale far beyond policy cycles, election cycles, or anyone's career.

Ranger Neral: We call it patient management.

He gives a dry half-shrug.

Ranger Neral: Mostly we are being patient while the land keeps blowing away.

