@duststorm_ask_root_cause
title: Ask what the real misunderstanding is
max-visits: 1

Me: So what is the real misunderstanding?

Facilyn folds the map closed with two fingers.

Facilyn: That the eastern flats are failing because no one cares too little.

Facilyn: In truth, they are failing because people are applying the wrong paradigm very carefully.

Facilyn: The reserve is managed as if total rest and very long-term rewilding were enough. When that predictably disappoints, fire is used to clear the symptoms. But the root problem remains: the soil is not being kept covered, old grasses are oxidising instead of breaking down biologically, the water cycle is weakening, and recovery is too slow for this brittle climate.

Ranger Neral: We know how to protect a boundary. We know how to ban things. We know how to write burn plans.

He looks at the broken stem beside your cup.

Ranger Neral: What we do not know how to do is make this dead grass break down biologically before the flats turn it into dust.

